Reasoning: The paper deals with the implementation of a failure detector in a distributed system, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of packets and channels suggests a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The study of feasibility and efficiency of the implementation involves algorithms and data structures, which are part of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The investigation of reliability and timeliness of channels relates to Control and Systems Engineering (cs.SY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
